===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|豸|苗|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p}}. The phonetic component perhaps points to the onomatopoeic nature of this word.

[[Wikipedia:Ma Xulun|Ma Xulun]] suggested that [[豸]] was the original character of 貓.

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|s=猫|t2=猫}}
[[Image:Alley the Calico.jpg|thumb|{{l|zh|[[一]][[隻]]貓}}]]
{{onomatopoeic|zh}}. Compare {{zh-l|喵|[[meow]], the [[onomatopoeic]] cry of a cat}}.

{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} reconstructs {{cog|och|-}} ''*mau'', reasoning that {{lang|zh|貓}}'s place among division II syllables results from its onomatopoeic nature instead of an {{cog|och|-}} medial ''*-r-''; onomatopoeia is also responsible for the {{zh-l|陰平}} tone instead of the expected {{zh-l|陽平}}.

